sections.description: Explore the general diet of raccoons, including their omnivorous nature and the variety of foods they consume, such as fruits, insects, and small animals.
Investigate whether raccoons include squirrels in their diet, discussing the circumstances under which they might prey on them.

sections.header: The Relationship Between Raccoons and Squirrels
sections.description: Analyze the ecological relationship between raccoons and squirrels, including competition for resources and potential predation.
Examine how raccoons hunt and forage for food, including their techniques and strategies that might involve hunting squirrels.
Discuss the natural defenses that squirrels have against predators like raccoons, including their agility and nesting habits.
Look at how raccoons compare to other predators, such as skunks, in terms of their hunting habits and prey preferences.

sections.header: Conclusion: Raccoons and Their Role in the Ecosystem
sections.description: Summarize the role of raccoons in the ecosystem, their dietary habits, and the impact they have on squirrel populations.
